Hello!

This workflow is pretty straight forward. It is mainly prompt and play. 

However, there are some things you should know. This workflow can work on a 12GB at minimum. It works as tested, It will take TIME to render. Hence, why the preview chooser has beem added.

Before going to use this, here are where I found my models. One of them is 700 buzz, but if you have another or your own, feel free to use it.

Below are the models I use. This workflow works well with furries and humans, however yoou may need to switch settings around. Please refer to the settings of the model in how to use them.



Model 1: Use A toony model of your choice. For humans, I use HomoSimileXL, WaiNaiNSFW or BoyTakudreamMerge.

For furries, I use Yiffy NoobAI or FurryToon

The realism Models are Willy's Noob AI, Ratatoskr Illustrious and Stable Yogi

IT IS IMPOPRTANT THAT IF YOU ARE USING THESE MODELS, YOU FOLLOW THEIR INSTRUCTIONS

Willy -> https://civitai.com/models/1143097/willys-noob-realism

Now, when it comes to furries, the controlnet is the most important. Leave them as they are but if you are not getting what you are looking for, tweak them a small amount. 

The best method I found, is keeping the strenght matching the end percentage. Somewhere between 0.6 and 0.75 for both is your best bet, otherwise, weird colours come out. Usually, the default I left them at works.

For humans, in the 3D controlnet, I use 0.75, and for furries I use 0.6 - Certain times, 0.8 works in 2.5D - Test what works for you!

ALSO - IMPORTANT -  THE EMBEDDINGS! Only use this with the stable YOGI for HUMANS! WHEN YOU ARE DOING FURRIES, BYPASS THIS!!! Unless your furry model uses embeddings, do not use it with furries or you will get weird looking outputs (Ive seen the horrors)

For the furry ones, I Use Ratato, Comes in handy for Humans, creatures and monsters!!

Where the 2D and 3D details are, put the embeddings there for the second model, otherwise you will get the embeddings travelling through the main prompt and that will fuck with things.



Upscalers are a case by case basis. I have put in the defaults whcih can be used in the workflow. However, when using ultralythics - use the default yolo for humans and only replace it WHEN YOU SWITCH to furries otherwise you will get strasnge faces.

REGARDING LORAS

Certain loras will make this look.... weird. You may need to play around with different controlnets,
For weird characters like Homer Simpson or something, write the changes you needed. Certain times,, certain characters dont work - this is your best bet. Sometimes, using other art styles helps bring out the realistic one. Experiment :3.
